# RULE 03 — DISPLAY ID FORMATS (LOCKED)

All display IDs are server-generated only. The frontend never composes a display ID. The user never edits one.

## Format table (locked)

| Entity | Format | Example |
|--------|--------|---------|
| Load | `L-{n}` | L-12047 |
| Driver Bill | `B-{load_number}` | B-L-12047 |
| Settlement | `S-YYYY-NNNN` | S-2026-0185 |
| Cash Advance | `CA-YYYY-NNNN` | CA-2026-0033 |
| Factoring Advance | `FA-YYYY-NNNN` | FA-2026-1842 |
| Work Order | `WO-{UNIT}-{TYPE}-{MM-DD-YYYY}-{NNNN}-{V5}` | WO-T169-IS-05-06-2026-0035-23914 |

## WO format detailed spec (Jorge confirmed chat 2026-05-06)

### Segments

- `{UNIT}` — `master_data.units.display_id` (e.g., T169, T177)
- `{TYPE}` — source_type code (2 chars, see source types below)
- `{MM-DD-YYYY}` — leading zeros, 4-digit year
- `{NNNN}` — per-unit cumulative LIFETIME sequence (4-digit zero-padded; NEVER resets)
- `{V5}` — last 5 chars of vendor invoice# OR vendor WO#, for cross-reference safety

### Source types (7)

| Code | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| IS | Internal Shop (IH35 own shop, non-tire) |
| ES | External Shop |
| AC | Accident (linked to safety accident report) |
| ET | External Tires (Loves, TA, Pilot, etc.) |
| RT | Roadside Tires (vendor came to truck) |
| IT | Internal Tires (IH35 own shop, tire-specific) |
| RS | Roadside Service (non-tire roadside: tow, jump, breakdown) |

### V5 selection rule

- For ES/AC/ET/RT/RS: last 5 chars of `external_vendor_invoice_number` (preferred) OR `external_vendor_wo_number` (if invoice not yet entered). Use whichever is set first; lock V5 once set.
- For IS/IT with parts: last 5 chars of FIRST `parts_invoice_links.vendor_invoice_number` for the WO (FIFO order by `created_at`)
- For IS/IT with `labor_only_no_parts = true`: literal string `LABOR`
- If vendor reference shorter than 5 chars: zero-pad on left (e.g., invoice "42" → "00042")
- For pending vendor entry: literal `PEND0`
- For backfilled rows: literal `LEGCY`

### Refresh rule

V5 is recomputed when:
- WO created with vendor reference (initial)
- Vendor invoice number changed BEFORE completion
- First `parts_invoice_links` added to IS/IT WO (recompute V5)

V5 is IMMUTABLE after WO transitions to `status='completed'`.

### Sequence rule

`{NNNN}` is per-unit cumulative across ALL source types, lifetime — never resets.

Example for unit T169:
- WO-T169-IS-03-15-2026-0033-78321
- WO-T169-AC-04-02-2026-0034-LT441
- WO-T169-IS-05-06-2026-0035-23914
- WO-T169-ET-05-08-2026-0036-08821

Unit T177 has its own independent counter starting at 0001.
